    {
      "id": "PopularPost219275",
      "post_content": "How doesn't the flavor make sense? He's a watchmen. He guards things, hence defender and warrior. He has the standard werewolf transformation effect, which does go counter to the red, but it makes sense from the perspective of flavor since all werewolves transform the same way (so far). He has such high toughness probably because it's taking into account the walls and armor protecting him. And his power is low because that's normal for archers. Really from a flavor perspective is the only way he makes sense, because really he should be white.",
